review_blob: On bottle. Aroma of coffee and cacao. Nice dark color with consistent head. Taste of coffee and slightly to vanilla. Very consistent. Good one
Tasted on tap. Nice dark imperial porter. Little notes of vanilla, chocolate and wood. Smooth. Nice balanced. Very good
beer_name: Yria / Hanscraft and Co Achtung! Imperial Porter

review_blob: On tap. Quite sweet and a little alcoholic. Nice aroma of tropical fruits. Well balanced. Slightly bitter
On can 33cl . Nice bitter pale ale. Really refreshing. Plenty of hops. Medium carbonation
Nice beer. Some bitterness in a refreshing wheat beer. Well balanced. Somehow sorry for an ipa.
On tap. Dark brown with nice head. Alcoholic smell and taste. Nice smoke aftertaste.
Orange color. Very little head. Nice smell. Nice combinaron of sourness strawberry and wine. Good one
On tap. Black as night. Nice dark head. Greatt aroma, tofee, chocolate, bourbon. God taste a bit Alcoholic . Excellent beer.
beer_name: Flying Dog Wild Dog Barrel-Aged Gonzo

review_blob: On 33 cl bottle. Expected much more. Nice reddish color with a thick head. Too sweet for me.
On tap at Valencia on tap. Frutal and very aromatic. Really hoppy and fresh. Very good.
Bottled on July 2013. No head. Brownish color. Medium body. Expected much more from this beer.
beer_name: De Molen Rasputin Buffalo Trace BA

review_blob: from can. Really nice and fresh IIPA. Piny and citrus notes. Quite resin. Long lasting bitterness. The alcohol is well hidden for being 8.8. Really impressed for my 3rd Australian beer in life

On bottle @Valencia On Tap. Really impressive beer. Starts sweet with cacao and vanilla flavours. Just when it seems to be too sweet, the chili appears to give you hottness and cut the sweetness. The alcohol is not too present.
